wiki.summary: “Pineapple” is a song by Colombian singer Karol G for her second studio album “OCEAN”. The song is titled Pineapple because of a dream that Karol G had in English. She uploaded a video on Instagram Live, where she states: “One day I saw a lot of pineapples. I had a dream about pineapples, and I woke up and said that I wanted my song to be titled pineapple.” She dreamed that the video would be in the jungle filled with pineapples and gorgeous women of all kinds. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Pineapple” is a song by Colombian singer Karol G for her second studio album “OCEAN”. The song is titled Pineapple because of a dream that Karol G had in English. She uploaded a video on Instagram Live, where she states: “One day I saw a lot of pineapples. I had a dream about pineapples, and I woke up and said that I wanted my song to be titled pineapple.” She dreamed that the video would be in the jungle filled with pineapples and gorgeous women of all kinds. And that the Island would be called “Pineapple Island.” Once she had written the song, she realized that it did not include the word pineapple, but it had already been written and so it was titled that.
